<section id="command-pitch">
<title>PITCH</title>
<indexterm><primary>PITCH</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PITCH</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the angle of the turtle's pitch in degrees.
It is important to <link linkend="understand-your-orientation-in-3D">understand your orientation in 3D</link>.
</para>
<para>
PITCH is designed to run in <link linkend="command-perspective">PERSPECTIVE</link> mode.
In 2D modes, PITCH outputs 0.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETPITCH 90
SHOW PITCH</userinput>
90
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>


<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-setpitch">SETPITCH</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>


</variablelist>
</section>
